* Add UI.print() method

No functional changes yet.

* Shift Parse.parse() exception printing to UI

Cascaded all Parse.parse() exceptions upwards to be printed by UI.printError(Exception e) within Duke.run()

* Add UI output indentation

The idea is that UI.print(String printString) will automatically handle printing lines outside every output by the program, and will also indent all output to clearly differentiate between user input and program output.

* Extract TaskList.searchForTask to FindCommand.execute()

We want to make TaskList just a dumb container, any smarter processing should be done within the Command objects' execute() methods.

* Extract printing of FindCommand to UI.print()

* Extract TaskList.printList() to Command.execute()

Ideally I believe we should have an explicit ListCommand class that executes this, but for now this should make dealing with UI output easier.

* Add DoneCommand class

Also extract TaskList.markItemAsDone() method

* Add DeleteCommand class

Also extract TaskList.deleteTask() method

* Add explicit ListCommand class
